  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Colic and rectal resection represents a majority of hospitalizations in visceral surgery. The
      objective of this study was to evaluate the prognostic of inflammatory markers dosage (CRP,
      procalcitonin and venous lactate) on the postoperative recovery after colorectal surgery and
      on the length of stay.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
